content.detailedDescription:
While standing on the deck, i noticed a beam of light over my head some distance away. after some time passed i realized it was not moving. i took a picture with my cell phone because i simply thought it unusual, and thought no more about it. yesterday while i was going through some pictures taken while traveling, i noticed something in the corner of the light picture. i enlarged and enhanced , enlarged and enhanced. some one who knows more about what they are looking at needs to see these pictures.  there are defined lines like maps, colors all over, windows?,and so much more i cant explain. it appears to be very ,very ,very, large.  i wasnt shaken when i took the picture because i thought it was just a light, but i am shaken now. i still havent managed to view all of the photos as i scan around enhancing one area at a time, it is extremely detailed. 

when i walked back into the house that night the object was still there and still hadnt moved for maybe hours.
content.summary: Thought it was just a beam of light, but it is more detailed than i can describe.

content.detailedDescription: I was taking the garbage out at about 8:30pm in athens,il when i clearly noticed 12 orbs in the sky, they were very bright. i then noticed that it was actually 4 objects each containing 3 orbs. i immediately knew it was a ufo knowing. 1 object took off south so rapid i only saw a streak of light. 1 object just disappeared out of nowhere. 2 remained for about 2-3 minutes just hovering. i ran and got my mother and we watched them together for about another 40seconds-1minute before they flew south towards petersburg,il just like the first object just a streak of light and no sound. i believe these orbs were in a disc shape or a rounded triangle. these were not human, these were extraterrestrial. i've seen videos of similar orbs but these were very very close and low on the horizon and a clear sky. soon after i lost site of these objects 2 black choppers flew over head and numerous jets, these were military aircraft that i believe were chasing these ufo's.
content.summary: 3 sets of orbs observed close

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my living room, reading. it was a sunny afternoon. something caught my eye that made me look out the window. i saw 3 round objects traveling sw. they appeared to be moving slowly. i have no idea how high they were but they were low enough for me to see that they looked round, that they looked white and that the sun was reflecting off of them. they were not in any kind of formation. i was very excited to see this as i had no idea what they could be.  suddenly one of them broke off from the group and shot straight up and out of sight at a very high rate of speed.  as soon as that happened the two remaining balls took off west, going in a straight line at an extremely high rate of speed. 
the next night, 12/30/14 my husband was in our back yard and saw 3 very large green lights (round). it was after midnight, maybe 12:30am. he grabbed his camera took video of them as they just seemed to be hovering, not moving. the video however looks as if they're going crazy with movement but that was from my husband's hand shaking. he said they were stationary and not moving. after about 3 or 4 minutes, one by one they just faded out until they were gone.  my husband was telling our neighbor about it and she stated that she too had seen them and she was very excited about it. "what were they".  the next night 1/1/14 they were back again only at a closer distance. i went out when my husband called for me. i can't determine the distance but my husband again got them on video and we noticed that there was absolutely no sound coming from them. as with the night before, one by one they eventually faded out until they were gone. so for 3 days in a row they same number of round objects were here.
content.summary: 3 round objects. one shot straight up, 2 shot west at high rate.

content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Bright lights behind the trees and i was flashing light back at it and then its lights would get brighter....When i walked closer...It woul hide..

content.detailedDescription:
I was looking east towards the san fernando valley, from my back yard in agoura hills, ca. the time was approx. 9:15 pm. i was observing orion on a great clear night. a very large light suddenly appeared, directly in my view at a pretty low altitude. it was as if someone flipped a switch to turn it on. i would estimate that the object was in the san fernando valley between calabasas and woodland hills. (again,just an estimate)  the bright light changed color from blue-green to some amber-orange. the light was stationary for a brief time and then, at an amazing speed, darted from the east directly towards my position west. the bright, large craft was at a low altitude. (on a daily basis, there is a continuous flight pattern of planes, flying past/over my location, descending eastward and southeastward to land at lax, john wayne, and/or other airports.) this craft was much lower, i would estimate less than 3000 feet or less.

the craft flew towards my position and ended up, to the left of my field of vision. the ufo's flight path, covered my complete field of view (as i turned my head as it passed) flying from it's position eastward, past me to the opposite horizon in the west/north west, until it was out of sight) this happened in less than 2 seconds. an amazing speed, and stayed at a constant altitude and direction. again, an incredible speed, no noise and the object looked large (larger than the light field produced my incoming planes at night, at higher altitudes !! this was not a comet or meteorite, as i observe meteor showers often.
i hope that others witnessed this incredible ufo. i'll be watching the skies more often.
content.summary: looking east towards sf valley, light appeared, hoverd, then flew at incredible speed towards my location, continued at constant elevation fast!

content.detailedDescription:

when i took the picture i did not see anything. the frame before and after have no markings, i have taken over 10,000 pictures with this camera (canon 650d fitted with a canon 15 to 85 zoom) and have had no similar markings. the day was very windy, visibility was good, a forest was 600 to 700 feet below and the area we were walking in is short rough scrub/grassland, the spots of white in the far hillside are sheep, this might give an idea of scale. the shutter speed was 160th sec at f7.1 at 15.0mm wide angle, 100 iso, image size was 18mp.
i am familiar with the use of photoshop but nothing has been altered from the original image apart from contrast, saturation and crop to enable a large zoom image. the first two images have enhancement and the second two are the original image, i can supply the full size original file if requested.

content.detailedDescription: At 5:05 a.M. dec. 29th. while walking towards my truck i saw commercial jets coming my direction which were out to the west. the jets were clearly visible, which is quite common because of their lights. it was still dark out. i had a sudden urge to look up and saw an orange glow. the glow was elongated or rectangular in shape. at first i thought there was a large piece of paper caught in the wind because of the movement of the glow. this object was moving at a fast rate heading south east and was reflecting the city lights and ground glow because of the snow cover.. it was completely silent and was fast as a jet. it was positioned lengthwise in the sky as it flew by. there were clouds forming to the south east. i know it was under the cloud layer because i watched it fly under them.. it was 1/2" x 1/4" at arms length when it was directly above me. i watched it fly farther and farther away until it was out of view.. clearly under the clouds.. it took 15 seconds or so from first observing it "over head" and when it went out of view.. what was really strange about it is was completely quiet.. the glow on the object moved differently then the object moved. then it dawned on me it was reflecting all the lights below it. the glow was fading in and out at random as do the ground lights.. like i said.. how can something fly right overhead and low not make any noise and go that fast... it was clearly reflecting the ground and if i didn't look up when i did i never would have seen it.
content.summary: I saw an object above me reflecting the ground lights rectangular in shape going south east

content.detailedDescription: I was walking easterly from my driveway to the back house after 9:00pm or so and noticed a flashing reddish-yellow light in the low se sky.  i thought it may be a plane on fire but it kept a straight horizontal path. it appeared to slow down for a second and then kept streaking on its path. i ran in the front house got my binoculars and ran back outside.  it was still there on its path traveling west. i was facing south as i looked in the binoculars and saw a fuzzy orange oval-like object. it began to dim its light.  i looked again with my own eyes but it was gone. i didn't get creeped out about it just curiously fascinated.  i know what i saw even if it didn't get reported on the news.
content.summary: A red and yellow flashing object like a plane on fire streaked across the sky then disapeared.

content.detailedDescription: While star gazing using 15\70 binoculars we saw a abnormal light in the sky seemed to be about 5 to 8 miles away couldn't make out a definitive shape.52 degrees nw. red light was hovering and moving up and down then moved across the sky to 60 degrees nw, while moving it turned green. the object then returned back to its original spot we first saw it at. when changing direction it did not turn like a plane or helicopter it simply changed direction... we live in the san diego international airport flight path, when the object was in the sky we witnessed three airliners go off their flight path to avoid the object. one plane turned south west one turned north and the last plane seemed to ascend over the object. then the light descended and was out of view. there are 4 of us that all saw the same thing.
content.summary: Hovering red light and then turned green as it moved and back to red

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home on towerline road, and as i stopped at the stop sign at towerline & toboggan road, i looked both way, but as i looked left, i noticed a few pulsating yellow-orange lights, that were kind of far away, but were still a little under the size of a baseball. as i started away from the stop sign, more lights appeared, seemingly out of nowhere. at this point in time, all of the 6 total lights were spread out. but as i continues driving, i decided to pull off on a side road, i believe it was hilst road off of towerline. and i slowly idled forward, and watched the 6 lights slowly get closer together, until it appeared that 3 were touching, making up 2 ships, with 3 lights each. then i noticed the road ahead was really snowy, so i started to turn around to head back the other way, and when i pulled into the field entrance on the right hand side of the road, i looked back up into the sky to my left, and all of the lights were gone, i looked all over the sky after that, but there was no trace of them, they had just disappeared. it was unlike any lights in the sky i had ever seen before, and i am 100% convinced that they were not human!
content.summary: 6 seperate lights, that combined made 2, 3 light objects

content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription:
I am on a hunting lease approximately 12 miles sw of comanche, tx on hwy 573.  the area is located within an electronic gunnery range used by military aircraft from both carswell and dyess afb; it is somewhat equidistant from both bases.  in the past i have observed f-16, f-15, and b-1 aircraft in the area with the fighters ejecting flares as part of their evasive actions used in dog fighting.  on the date of the sighting, the military aircraft had performed aerial maneuvers in the area for the first time in 3 months, due to the sequester.  the aircraft ceased flying around 6:30pm that day.  the sky was cloudless, no wind, and only a sliver of the moon shining.  i had finished watching a dvd movie (memphis belle) which i have seen numerous times.  the time was 9:45pm, when i stepped outside of my camper trailer, because i was hearing coyotes at a very close distance to our camp.  i was looking directly west in the direction of the coyotes, when i noticed some strange, flashing lights above the treeline to the northwest.  i watched for several minutes and could see the faint outline of a craft - it appeared to have a rectangular shaped box with curved edges on the top of the craft, the fuselage was cigar shaped.  blue lights about the size of a beach ball were on each side of the box and were randomly flashing and were not in unison. whereas, the fuselage contained a row of 4 or 5 louvered, white lights across the bottom that "glimmered" as though shining off of water.  the closest lake is 3.5 miles away and to the northeast from the camp. i decided to go inside and get my camera, however when i came back outside, the craft was gone.  i heard no noise nor did i see the craft anywhere in the area - it had quietly disappeared.  there was no other people in camp, and the house located directly north from our camp did not appear to have anyone at home - no lights in the house were on.  

i never experienced seeing a ufo, although our camp is approximately 40 miles west of the dublin/stephenville sighting in 2008.  also, i should point out that i am involved with bigfoot investigations and research. i have been doing field research for 12 years, so feel that i am an expert observer with attention to detail.
content.summary: Spotted an object hovering above the trees.

content.detailedDescription: We invited the craft here in meditation and cts - ce-5. the 4 of us then observed the sky and used a strong flashlight to signal to them. we also used the tones provided on dr. steven greer's et contact app. we also received similar contact around a week before in a different country location, which were the same sort of objects although much more frequently and much more sightings. the craft/ufo we saw appeared to be the size of a fairly bright star and gave off a much brighter light. the ufo's would suddenly appear from nothing really but as it appeared from nothing it caught our eyes with a flash but that was because it came into visibility so fast. it then traveled across the sky extremely fast then suddenly disappeared with no trace. the appearance and disappearance of these objects lasted around 1 and half second but was able to travel a substantial distance in that time. this night we saw around 5 of these objects and each sighting we reacted in a excited but calm manner. all sightings occurred in different places of the sky. these sighting were in kangaroo island-australia.
content.summary: Ce-5- white star like object darting in and out of visibility.

content.detailedDescription:
Went outside talking to wife when (facing east) i noticed a lot of activity in the air.We live under b'ham (bhx)england flight path as it happened there was an inbound aircraft (east-west), my wife thought at first this was the one i was on about,also i can observe major flight paths traversing the country nth/sth/east & west being quite central.      first thought it was a slower and lower than usual passenger jet, then i noticed the three lights where all in a line blinking at a different rate to the flash of a modern strobe light on current passenger/private and military jets normally when observed from my back yard in the evening,also they appeared to be oblong in between the blinking.
 the object had no discernible shape viewing it from a distance,it was on a straight line course slower than a passenger jet ? but the three lights definitely where not strobe and where very bright blinking rather than flashing, i would assume the course to be s/westish as definitely not the same as other sth bound aircraft also flying at that moment approx 5 in number ?  
 couldn't work out what it may have been possible military but the light blinking was odd ? i watched the ufo until it disappeared out of eyesight, i had no reaction really felt calm enough to then just go back inside to make a cup of tea,then thought about reporting to mufon-uk.
 can i add this is my first report,i do know the difference from  a ufo and an alien space craft as until you identify anything flying it is a ufo.
i also know how to spot a sattlelight,meteor and aircraft (being an enthusiast), can i add that i have an open mind and do believe that we are not the only intelligence in the universe and anything is possible.
content.summary: Observed 3 bright white lights(not strobe !)blinking,other aircraft with strobes in visinity.
